The @url-sanitize/clearurls package ships two layers with different licenses:

1. Source code in src/ (adapter, types, exports) — MIT License
2. Bundled rule data in data/data.json, derived from the ClearURLs Rules
   repository (https://github.com/ClearURLs/Rules) — LGPL-3.0-only

The bundled data is reproduced from the ClearURLs project. ClearURLs is a
trademark of its respective authors; this package is not an official ClearURLs
product. See NOTICE for upstream attribution.

For the LGPL-3.0-only text, see: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl-3.0.txt

